<opml version="1.0" xmlns:sx="http://www.microsoft.com/schemas/rss/sse"><head><title>Indistractable</title><dateCreated>2024-01-25T14:36:17</dateCreated><dateModified>2024-01-25T14:39:31</dateModified><ownerName>cloudobserver@gmail.com</ownerName></head><body><outline text="The problem"><outline text="When attempting something difficult, there is discomfort"><sx:sync version="1" id="e8tSUa99JEm1bxxmZNElPg==" /></outline><outline text="Distraction is a way to avoid or delay discomfort"><sx:sync version="1" id="DRrq23qRaEeCjbiy5EtJeQ==" /></outline><outline text="Distracting behavior tends to be -"><outline text="- easy, not confusing"><sx:sync version="1" id="Vrcl6zNBpEaXom85KFVugg==" /></outline><outline text="- something I can control and succeed at "><sx:sync version="1" id="ok7J/K8KzkGSwnRj1Dg1JQ==" /></outline><outline text="- non-productive"><sx:sync version="1" id="OY3VwVgrDEWBOhA4vzbriw==" /></outline><outline text="- may be productive but not urgent - do it later"><sx:sync version="1" id="cFGbYWWo+U6qdtia+MZERg==" /></outline><outline text="- addicting"><sx:sync version="1" id="1l9ZdnLlnEuWN2/fccUlJg==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="7W8L5rWEWUyVCDyZ40ntjQ==" /></outline><outline text="How do I stay focused on a difficult task when escaping is so easy?"><sx:sync version="1" id="CA6sRIzhcEmWQICOLZBwxA==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="CsNBKPxyxEaJaFfCM47vHw==" /></outline><outline text="Notice the details"><outline text="How does distraction emerge in you?"><sx:sync version="1" id="7O0dAoQzb0y4eXgc74sz5A==" /></outline><outline text="Notice the craving for the distracting behavior"><sx:sync version="1" id="CR8POTFds0y+cMJKaMCE2w==" /></outline><outline text="Look for the emotion and/or discomfort that precedes the distraction"><sx:sync version="1" id="CuLChfqSHkeFVodcn6Vj1g==" /></outline><outline text="Such as anxiety, feeling restless, feeling incompetent, craving something"><sx:sync version="1" id="wkh3tuH63E+/XYBmi6ahFQ==" /></outline><outline text="Take notes. Use Distraction Tracker sheet"><sx:sync version="1" id="LvK+VPql9UKrIgL70qOuVQ==" /></outline><outline text="Be a witness - &quot;I feel a familiar tension in my chest. And I want to click on CNN.&quot;"><sx:sync version="1" id="ENJWCx0+6kiu3wK5DAdDIw==" /></outline><outline text="Do you experience a cycle of resisting, ruminating, and finally giving in to a desire?"><sx:sync version="1" id="Lo0Ujl6yL0ui9RaOV0KBZA==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="xRiW6v4Z9U+VvKVu51fZpQ==" /></outline><outline text="Ten minute rule"><outline text="It's dangerous to do some unhelpful behavior &quot;just for a second&quot;"><sx:sync version="1" id="geFPSxJ7lkOREDnAlqgb3g==" /></outline><outline text="I can do the thing but only after I wait ten minutes."><sx:sync version="1" id="g44UP7LsnUuVu+ZQUHUJUA==" /></outline><outline text="During the ten minutes, notice your sensations and ride them like a wave "><sx:sync version="1" id="XiWW4vSiIEepE1PNmyD9zg==" /></outline><outline text="Don't push anything away and also don't act on anything"><sx:sync version="1" id="lnybIHzhvEaNY92Jl/J11Q==" /></outline><outline text="Watch the craving as it crests and subsides"><sx:sync version="1" id="B0JdqUKnUE6qwglbf7gJmA==" /></outline><outline text="Imagine leaves floating down a stream. Place your thought on a leaf and let it float away, swirling in the current."><sx:sync version="1" id="Ub6zB4BX8EqJ2txmc6th7Q==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="AKxFEpgb6kitv8ixDDBq4Q==" /></outline><outline text="What's interesting here?"><outline text="Approach a familiar situation with fresh eyes, curiosity, creativity, humor"><sx:sync version="1" id="bStvyDuxVkeUQ4wGDplkGw==" /></outline><outline text="Pay full attention to find variability and challenges you didn't see before"><sx:sync version="1" id="7MYhu/OXh021v6KFPGpt6w==" /></outline><outline text="Pay close, foolish, even absurd attention to your task"><sx:sync version="1" id="dSCr/IuAoESAehFLCYBBkQ==" /></outline><outline text="Learn new things about it, transform it into an imaginary playground."><sx:sync version="1" id="akQjo4VxdUSaEGTg+vq8qg==" /></outline><outline text="What is interesting about it that you didn't notice before?"><sx:sync version="1" id="8cbtW/t30ECQxd3WkUKN3A==" /></outline><outline text="Find some aspect of the task that your mind can get hooked into"><sx:sync version="1" id="msguqVT+RE+n6DBeWqOh1w==" /></outline><outline text="Pose interesting questions"><sx:sync version="1" id="Xyt6K/V4JUKDhNIX9VdsKg==" /></outline><outline text="Look for new solutions to old problems"><sx:sync version="1" id="IjI+UYdbvECSDmUxW54XEA==" /></outline><outline text="What is mysterious about this? What do I want to know about this? What am I curious about?"><sx:sync version="1" id="jGjz/of7WES9U6RuaImz0g==" /></outline><outline text="Look for variability and novelty"><sx:sync version="1" id="jesOFnHTyEqpAVRxvDh3/Q==" /></outline><outline text="Do the task to a higher standard of excellence"><sx:sync version="1" id="vgkiCwX1rU29zYveIdiFzg==" /></outline><outline text="Example - Mowing the lawn"><outline text="How can I mow the lawn more efficiently?"><sx:sync version="1" id="397/WNTCokupC5lQmRpYbA==" /></outline><outline text="What is the optimum path for the mower?"><sx:sync version="1" id="glxCqd3TUkOaIJzqCzhd6w==" /></outline><outline text="Look for the interesting constraints"><sx:sync version="1" id="lo7y8L1e/E23S6IYtvJebQ==" /></outline><outline text="Can you beat your record time?"><sx:sync version="1" id="embuf1Y97USceOn9dtw/tQ==" /></outline><outline text="Understand how the grass grows and how to help it grow"><sx:sync version="1" id="95FPku2JI0eRrjUMrBh1Sw==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="etD1FhmWgUuskL29x9Esew==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="TbYHpCPV8UWAkQpb8J/P7Q==" /></outline><outline text="Will power"><outline text="You don't run out of will power"><sx:sync version="1" id="hUOuwW2lJE6Wzsrfja176Q==" /></outline><outline text="It does ebb and flow but it's not out of control"><sx:sync version="1" id="QMtXbvIeekqBil2IFdXAYw==" /></outline><outline text="You don't run out of calmness or excitement, likewise will power"><sx:sync version="1" id="8WHVMOVVkUiMnLp7fTLeIA==" /></outline><outline text="Is there a method to maximize will power?"><sx:sync version="1" id="j7ubdmjDj0iLIruD0oSymQ==" /></outline><outline text="Lack of motivation is temporary"><sx:sync version="1" id="wOkZDCNf1kObr6ujpXRK8Q==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="6O1+uFO1S0e2asKhTm6rIw==" /></outline><outline text="Define your values"><outline text="What vibration do you want to give to the world?"><sx:sync version="1" id="6XOk2pEn+EqBOfaG6Fmzqw==" /></outline><outline text="What do you want to stand for?"><sx:sync version="1" id="y/SBf38x/0OPwJvCLF0TVw==" /></outline><outline text="How do you want to relate to the world?"><sx:sync version="1" id="ITjq5xjKjUWdLTuJDDMCTw==" /></outline><outline text="What are the attributes of the person you want to be?"><sx:sync version="1" id="Pjo2Ea8evEyutP/hDKePag==" /></outline><outline text="Create a schedule that includes activities aligned with your values"><sx:sync version="1" id="lqO+a16pIEOLGKFj3/jkDQ==" /></outline><sx:sync version="1" id="Qsi5jnXlOUmXAhvz/fgG5A==" /></outline></body></opml>
